steps.instruction:
For a more step-by-step guide go [here](https://www.kingarthurflour.com/blog/2010/07/26/make-french-macarons-at-home-mais-oui)

1. Process the almond flour and the confectioners' sugar in a food processor for 20 seconds
2. Sift to remove any large pieces and to aerate the mixture
3. Separate the eggs and put the whites in the bowl you'll use to whip them
    - Don't start whipping yet, but add a pinch each of salt and cream of tartar
4. Combine the water and granulated sugar in a small saucepan
5. Stir over medium heat until the sugar dissolves, then bring to a rapid boil
6. Boil for 2 minutes; the temperature of the syrup should reach between 235°F and 240°F
7. Take the syrup off the heat
8. Immediately start whipping the egg whites, using an electric mixer
9. When they hold a curved peak on the end of the beater, stop, grab the pan of hot syrup, resume beating, and pour the syrup steadily into the whites as you beat
10. Continue beating until the meringue is smooth, glossy, and forms soft peaks
11. Fold in the almond flour/sugar until everything is evenly combined, then start stirring
    - This will thin the mixture
12. Stir until the batter runs in ribbons that disappear back into the mass in 10 to 20 seconds
    - Test frequently, and stop stirring when you reach this point
13. Use a teaspoon cookie scoop or a pastry bag to deposit a generous teaspoon-sized round blob of batter onto a parchment-covered baking sheet
14. The cookie should flatten out, rather than remain in a tall blob
15. If it doesn't spread, stir the batter some more; your goal is a disc-like, fairly flat cookie
16. Repeat with the remainder of the batter
17. Since the cookies won't spread as they bake, you can position them fairly close together
18. Allow to rest in a dry place with good air circulation (a counter top is fine) until you can gently touch the tops and come away with a clean finger, about 2 hours
19. Towards the end of the resting time, preheat the oven to 275°F
20. Bake the cookies for 25 to 30 minutes, till firm on the top
21. Remove them from the oven, and cool completely on sheet
22. Use a thin spatula to carefully separate them from the parchment or foil
23. Spread half the cookies with jam, ganache, frosting, nut butter, or any combination of fillings your heart desires
24. Top with the remaining cookies
